### (1) Translation of the Story  
King Wǔ of Wei had made a decision that was perfectly appropriate, and none of his ministers could match his wisdom. After court, he wore a pleased expression. Wu Qi approached and asked, “Have you ever heard the words of King Chuang of Chu? Perhaps they could be shared with you?”  
King Wǔ replied, “What did King Chuang say?”  
Wu Qi answered, “Once, when King Chuang made a decision that was perfectly appropriate, none of his ministers could match him. After court, he wore a worried expression. Shen Gong Wuchen asked, ‘Your Majesty, why do you look so troubled after court?’  
King Chuang replied, ‘When I make a decision and none of my ministers can match me, this is why I am worried. As Zhong Liu once said: *“A ruler who can find a teacher among his ministers will become a king, one who finds a friend will become a hegemon, one who finds a skeptic will survive, but one who plans alone and sees no one as his equal will perish.”* Now, though I am unworthy, none of my ministers can match me. Does this mean my state is near ruin? That is why I am worried.’  
King Chuang worried, but Your Majesty rejoices.”  
King Wǔ, taken aback, bowed twice and said, “Heaven has sent you to correct my mistake!”  

